
---


@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Person {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +dateOfBirth: Date
  +registrationDate: Date
  +waitingListPosition: Integer
}

class Inhabitant {
  +id: String
  +person: Person
  +currentStays: Set<Stay>
  +waitingListEntries: Set<WaitingListEntry>
}

class WaitingListEntry {
  +id: String
  +typeOfStay: String (RH/RNH/SF)
  +person: Person
  +position: Integer
}

class Category {
  +id: String
  +name: String (RH/RNH/SF)
  +pricePerMonth: Double
}

class Room {
  +id: String
  +department: Department
  +beds: Set<Bed>
}

class Department {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +rooms: Set<Room>
}

class Bed {
  +id: String
  +room: Room
  +category: Category
  +isAvailable: Boolean
}

class Stay {
  +id: String
  +inhabitant: Inhabitant
  +startDate: Date
  +endDate: Date
  +category: Category
  +isSuspended: Boolean
}

class Proposal {
  +id: String
  +waitingListEntry: WaitingListEntry
  +proposalDate: Date
  +status: String (Pending/Accepted/Rejected/Invalidated)
  +category: Category
}

class Invoice {
  +id: String
  +stay: Stay
  +issueDate: Date
  +dueDate: Date
  +totalAmount: Double
  +paidAmount: Double
  +outstandingAmount: Double
  +status: String (Pending/Paid/PartiallyPaid)
}

class Payment {
  +id: String
  +invoice: Invoice
  +amount: Double
  +paymentDate: Date
  +method: String
}

class Assessment {
  +id: String
  +person: Person
  +results: String
  +date: Date
  +typeOfStayRecommended: String
}

' Relationships

Person "1" -- "1" Inhabitant : has
Inhabitant "1" -- "0..*" WaitingListEntry : has
WaitingListEntry "1" -- "1" Proposal : is linked to
Proposal "1" -- "1" WaitingListEntry : is for
Proposal "1" -- "1" Category : recommends
Category "1" -- "0..*" Bed : has
Department "1" -- "0..*" Room : has
Room "1" -- "0..*" Bed : has
Inhabitant "1" -- "0..*" Stay : has
Stay "1" -- "1" Category : uses
Stay "1" -- "1" Inhabitant : belongs to
Invoice "1" -- "1" Stay : is for
Invoice "1" -- "0..*" Payment : has
Payment "1" -- "1" Invoice : is for
Assessment "1" -- "1" Person : is for
Assessment "1" -- "1" WaitingListEntry : determines

@enduml

---

### 🧾 Summary of Classes and Relationships

| Class Name        | Description |
|-------------------|-------------|
| **Person**        | Represents an individual with basic data like name, birth date, etc. |
| **Inhabitant**    | A registered person who may be in multiple stays. |
| **WaitingListEntry** | Entry for a person waiting for a specific type of stay. |
| **Category**      | Defines types of stays (RH, RNH, SF) and their prices. |
| **Room**          | A room in a department that contains beds. |
| **Department**    | A division within the home containing rooms. |
| **Bed**           | A bed in a room assigned to a category. |
| **Stay**          | A period during which an inhabitant resides in a bed. Can be suspended. |
| **Proposal**      | A suggestion made to a waiting list entry to accept a stay. |
| **Invoice**       | Monthly invoice for a stay. Can be partially paid or unpaid. |
| **Payment**       | An event representing a payment towards an invoice. |
| **Assessment**    | Evaluation of a person's needs to determine suitable stay type. |

---

### 📝 Notes:
- **Associations** are shown with multiplicity and labels.
- **Attributes** include both identifiers and relevant data fields.
- **Behavioral aspects** such as status (`Pending`, `Accepted`, `Rejected`) are modeled as properties.
- The system supports **suspended stays**, **waiting lists**, and **invoicing logic** for multiple concurrent stays with discounts.

